Iranian President Mahmoud Ahmadinejad plans to reach  Saudi Arabia  today to participate in
the summit of the Organization of Islamic Cooperation, the
state-run  Al Alam  television reported, citing Mohamed Furqani,
the head of international affairs at the presidential office.  The meeting of the 57-member organization is taking place
in the Muslim holy city of Mecca on Aug. 14-15, the television
report said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
